    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-12-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-12-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="559"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d559">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The President of the Council of People’s Commissars of the
                        Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stalin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to President <persName type="to"
                            >Roosevelt</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="24" type="source" xml:id="d559fn24">Copy obtained from the Franklin D.
                        Roosevelt Library, Hyde Park, N. Y.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-12-18">December 18,
                            1942</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I am very grateful to you for your readiness to help us. As to Anglo-American
                    air-squadrons with personnel, at the present moment the necessity of having them
                    sent to the Transcaucasia has passed. Now the major battles are and will be
                    developing at the central front and in the Voronezh area. I shall be very
                    grateful to you; if you expedite the delivery of planes, especially fighter
                    planes—without the personnel which is now extremely necessary to yourself—to be
                    used in the above-mentioned areas.</p>
                <p>The peculiar state of Soviet aviation is that we have more than enough fliers,
                    but not enough planes.</p>
            </div>
